org.apromore.plugin.impl

Class DefaultPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apromore.plugin.impl.DefaultPlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Plugin
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultPropertyAwarePlugin

    public abstract class DefaultPlugin
extends Object
implements Plugin

    Default implementation of an Apromore Plugin. Unless you are sure about it you should always use this implementation as superclass for your Plugin. It automatically reads reads meta data from a '.config' file. This file has to be in the 'ISO 8859-1' character encoding and follow all rules of a Java Properties file.

    The '.config' files has to be named according to the following rules and be placed in the '.' directory in the classpath of your plugin. The configuration file always end with '.config' and is prefixed by the canonical name of the Plugin class. (as returned by Class.getCanonicalName()) For example:

    org.apromore.plugin.DefaultPlugin.config for the DefaultPlugin

    Author:
    Felix Mannhardt (Bonn-Rhein-Sieg University oAS)
